Name one fictional character from a classic piece of literature or film who represents courage, strength, and resilience in the face of adversity, and provide a brief explanation of how this character embodies these traits.
A classic character that embodies courage is Captain James Kirk from Star Trek. As a leader of the USS Enterprise, he demonstrates bravery by continually standing up against adversaries like the Klingon Empire, Romulan Star Empire, and other threats to the Federation. His strength lies in his determination to protect humanity's interests while exploring new frontiers of space. Kirk's resilience is shown through his ability to recover from setbacks and continue striving for progress.
